Variation of Animals and Plants

00:08:21.740 --> 00:08:25.190 align:middle line:84%
Under Domestication,"
which is less well known

00:08:25.190 --> 00:08:28.400 align:middle line:84%
than his most famous book,
"The Origin of Species,"

00:08:28.400 --> 00:08:32.390 align:middle line:84%
he documents many cases of how
plant and animal breeders have

00:08:32.390 --> 00:08:36.890 align:middle line:84%
produced different varieties of
dogs and pigeons and cabbages

00:08:36.890 --> 00:08:39.440 align:middle line:90%
and so forth.

00:08:39.440 --> 00:08:42.049 align:middle line:84%
And he shows that
in many cases, there

00:08:42.049 --> 00:08:44.780 align:middle line:84%
are adaptations which
can be inherited.

00:08:44.780 --> 00:08:47.390 align:middle line:84%
For example, he wrote
a paper in Nature,

00:08:47.390 --> 00:08:51.350 align:middle line:84%
about a dog that he'd
been investigating

00:08:51.350 --> 00:08:53.510 align:middle line:90%
that was afraid of butchers.

00:08:53.510 --> 00:08:56.990 align:middle line:84%
And whenever it got near a
butcher shop, it was terrified.

00:08:56.990 --> 00:08:59.900 align:middle line:84%
And he discovered that
the father of that dog

00:08:59.900 --> 00:09:03.150 align:middle line:84%
had been maltreated
by a butcher,

00:09:03.150 --> 00:09:05.810 align:middle line:84%
and it had inherited
this fear of butchers.

00:09:05.810 --> 00:09:07.280 align:middle line:84%
Now, you see,
that's not possible

00:09:07.280 --> 00:09:09.650 align:middle line:90%
on regular genetic inheritance.

00:09:09.650 --> 00:09:14.240 align:middle line:84%
It's an acquired characteristic,
this fear of butchers.

00:09:14.240 --> 00:09:17.720 align:middle line:84%
And so that side of Darwin,
the Lamarckian side of Darwin,

00:09:17.720 --> 00:09:19.910 align:middle line:90%
was sort of airbrushed out.

00:09:19.910 --> 00:09:22.200 align:middle line:84%
And the neo-Darwinian
theory of evolution,

00:09:22.200 --> 00:09:26.420 align:middle line:84%
which is the current orthodoxy
is Darwin minus Lamarckian

00:09:26.420 --> 00:09:27.800 align:middle line:90%
inheritance.

00:09:27.800 --> 00:09:30.780 align:middle line:84%
But interestingly, it's all
recently come back again,

00:09:30.780 --> 00:09:36.110 align:middle line:84%
having been a taboo in biology,
under the rebranded name

00:09:36.110 --> 00:09:41.330 align:middle line:84%
of epigenetic inheritance,
where acquired characteristics,

00:09:41.330 --> 00:09:45.350 align:middle line:84%
it's now recognized that
they can indeed be inherited.

00:09:45.350 --> 00:09:49.490 align:middle line:84%
And one molecular
