00:10:28.160 --> 00:10:30.530 align:middle line:84%
And it's an old style
experiment in the sense

00:10:30.530 --> 00:10:32.720 align:middle line:84%
that male mice were
exposed to this,

00:10:32.720 --> 00:10:35.090 align:middle line:84%
and they were given a
minor electric shock

00:10:35.090 --> 00:10:36.590 align:middle line:90%
through their pores.

00:10:36.590 --> 00:10:38.750 align:middle line:84%
So whenever they
smelled acetophenone,

00:10:38.750 --> 00:10:40.850 align:middle line:90%
they were terrified.

00:10:40.850 --> 00:10:41.690 align:middle line:90%
Not surprisingly.

00:10:41.690 --> 00:10:44.570 align:middle line:84%
They knew it meant they'd
get an electric shock.

00:10:44.570 --> 00:10:46.670 align:middle line:84%
The researchers then
bred from these mice

00:10:46.670 --> 00:10:48.360 align:middle line:90%
using artificial insemination.

00:10:48.360 --> 00:10:51.720 align:middle line:84%
So there was no contact
between these fathers

00:10:51.720 --> 00:10:53.720 align:middle line:84%
and the mothers
and the children.

00:10:53.720 --> 00:10:58.580 align:middle line:84%
And they found that the
children and their grandchildren

00:10:58.580 --> 00:11:00.930 align:middle line:90%
were terrified of acetophenone.

00:11:00.930 --> 00:11:03.170 align:middle line:84%
So there'd been an
inheritance of this fear.

00:11:03.170 --> 00:11:05.180 align:middle line:84%
That's why the paper
is called inheriting

00:11:05.180 --> 00:11:07.580 align:middle line:90%
the fears of fathers.

00:11:07.580 --> 00:11:10.204 align:middle line:90%
Over just one generation.

00:11:10.204 --> 00:11:12.620 align:middle line:84%
That's something that would
have been completely ruled out

00:11:12.620 --> 00:11:17.240 align:middle line:84%
in 20th century biology, but is
now mainstream in 21st century

00:11:17.240 --> 00:11:18.560 align:middle line:90%
biology.

00:11:18.560 --> 00:11:22.340 align:middle line:84%
Now, whether that's
because of modifications

00:11:22.340 --> 00:11:25.760 align:middle line:84%
of the proteins
around the genes,

00:11:25.760 --> 00:11:27.680 align:middle line:84%
or whether it's
something more mysterious

00:11:27.680 --> 00:11:30.290 align:middle line:84%
like morphic resonance, or
whether it's a combination

00:11:30.290 --> 00:11:33.020 align:middle line:90%
of the two is not yet known.

00:11:33.020 --> 00:11:35.330 align:middle line:84%
But the interesting
thing is that now

00:11:35.330 --> 00:11:38.750 align:middle line:84%
the taboo has been lifted,
this kind of research

00:11:38.750 --> 00:11:39.980 align:middle line:90%
is going ahead.

00:11:39.980 --> 00:11:42.280 align:middle line:90%
It's treated as mainstream.

00:11:42.280 --> 00:11:44.570 align:middle line:84%
It's not particularly
controversial.

00:11:44.570 --> 00:11:49.670 align:middle line:84%
And this actually is one of the
most exciting areas of biology

00:11:49.670 --> 00:11:51.890 align:middle line:90%
at the moment, epigenetics.

00:11:51.890 --> 00:11:54.470 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVID: Well, I know Johns
Hopkins University has

00:11:54.470 --> 00:11:58.070 align:middle line:84%
