00:15:34.700 --> 00:15:35.609 align:middle line:90%
in the brain.

00:15:35.609 --> 00:15:37.150 align:middle line:84%
And as I'm sure
you're aware, there's

00:15:37.150 --> 00:15:39.740 align:middle line:84%
many cases of
near-death experience.

00:15:39.740 --> 00:15:44.510 align:middle line:84%
And people see examples of
things happening in the room,

00:15:44.510 --> 00:15:46.440 align:middle line:84%
but their body is
clinically dead.

00:15:46.440 --> 00:15:47.240 align:middle line:90%
>>SHELDRAKE: Yes.

00:15:47.240 --> 00:15:49.191 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVID: So what do
you think is happening?

00:15:49.191 --> 00:15:50.690 align:middle line:84%
>>SHELDRAKE: You
see, I think we all

00:15:50.690 --> 00:15:53.300 align:middle line:84%
have the experience of
the body which is not

00:15:53.300 --> 00:15:56.210 align:middle line:84%
the same as our normal body,
that is separable from it,

00:15:56.210 --> 00:15:57.590 align:middle line:90%
in our dreams.

00:15:57.590 --> 00:15:59.480 align:middle line:90%
Every night, all of us dream.

00:15:59.480 --> 00:16:00.950 align:middle line:90%
Most of us forget our dreams.

00:16:00.950 --> 00:16:03.484 align:middle line:84%
But when you
remember dreams, then

00:16:03.484 --> 00:16:05.900 align:middle line:84%
what happens in the dreams is
that you're going to places,

00:16:05.900 --> 00:16:09.770 align:middle line:84%
you're talking to people, you're
running, walking, dancing,

00:16:09.770 --> 00:16:12.479 align:middle line:90%
swimming, sometimes flying.

00:16:12.479 --> 00:16:14.270 align:middle line:84%
You can do all these
things in your dreams.

00:16:14.270 --> 00:16:17.120 align:middle line:84%
But clearly, the dream body
that you're doing these with

00:16:17.120 --> 00:16:18.680 align:middle line:84%
is not the same as
the physical body

00:16:18.680 --> 00:16:21.950 align:middle line:90%
which is lying asleep in bed.

00:16:21.950 --> 00:16:25.760 align:middle line:84%
So I think all of us have a kind
of parallel body, a dream body.

00:16:25.760 --> 00:16:29.870 align:middle line:84%
And in out-of-the-body
experiences and in near-death

00:16:29.870 --> 00:16:33.050 align:middle line:84%
experiences, I think what
happens is people, as it were,

00:16:33.050 --> 00:16:36.690 align:middle line:84%
shift into this dream body,
which they've got anyway.

00:16:36.690 --> 00:16:37.490 align:middle line:90%
We all have them.

00:16:37.490 --> 00:16:38.860 align:middle line:90%
It's not that mysterious.

00:16:38.860 --> 00:16:42.530 align:middle line:84%
It's something we're familiar
with from our own experience.

00:16:42.530 --> 00:16:45.200 align:middle line:84%
And somehow, their
center of consciousness

00:16:45.200 --> 00:16:47.825 align:middle line:84%
moves out of the physical
body, as it does in dreams.

00:16:47.825 --> 00:16:50.630 align:middle line:90%


00:16:50.630 --> 00:16:52.460 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVID: So that's a
very real thing now

00:16:52.460 --> 00:16:54.660 align:middle line:90%
we can tangibly identify.

