00:19:54.540 --> 00:19:56.010 align:middle line:90%
but the activity of the brain.

00:19:56.010 --> 00:19:59.190 align:middle line:90%
It's all inside the head.

00:19:59.190 --> 00:20:01.640 align:middle line:84%
Another one is that the
laws of nature are fixed.

00:20:01.640 --> 00:20:04.060 align:middle line:84%
And I would say they're
more like habits.

00:20:04.060 --> 00:20:05.730 align:middle line:84%
So I was looking
at these dogmas,

00:20:05.730 --> 00:20:09.390 align:middle line:84%
looking at them in the light
of scientific discoveries

00:20:09.390 --> 00:20:13.920 align:middle line:84%
by science itself and showing
that these assumptions are not

00:20:13.920 --> 00:20:17.200 align:middle line:84%
valid and that if we
abandon these assumptions,

00:20:17.200 --> 00:20:18.840 align:middle line:84%
move on from them--
and they were all

00:20:18.840 --> 00:20:22.590 align:middle line:84%
set down in science between
the 17th and the 19th century.

00:20:22.590 --> 00:20:25.050 align:middle line:84%
Science has outgrown
these assumptions,

00:20:25.050 --> 00:20:27.960 align:middle line:84%
and yet, it's still locked into
this kind of materialist world

00:20:27.960 --> 00:20:29.070 align:middle line:90%
view--

00:20:29.070 --> 00:20:31.590 align:middle line:84%
that science can move
on, and all sorts

00:20:31.590 --> 00:20:34.740 align:middle line:84%
of new questions and new
research becomes possible.

00:20:34.740 --> 00:20:37.680 align:middle line:84%
Well, scientific fundamentalists
don't like this position.

00:20:37.680 --> 00:20:41.400 align:middle line:84%
And a lot of militant atheists
have linked their atheism

00:20:41.400 --> 00:20:43.920 align:middle line:84%
to a kind of scientific
fundamentalism.

00:20:43.920 --> 00:20:46.440 align:middle line:90%
Science isn't a set--

00:20:46.440 --> 00:20:49.050 align:middle line:84%
materialism isn't, for
them, a set of assumptions

00:20:49.050 --> 00:20:51.400 align:middle line:84%
or a worldview or
a belief system.

00:20:51.400 --> 00:20:53.280 align:middle line:90%
It's the truth.

00:20:53.280 --> 00:20:55.410 align:middle line:84%
So they think other
people have beliefs,

00:20:55.410 --> 00:20:57.120 align:middle line:90%
but they know the truth.

00:20:57.120 --> 00:21:00.710 align:middle line:84%
And some of them were deeply
offended by my TED Talk

00:21:00.710 --> 00:21:04.590 align:middle line:84%
and protested to TED that
they'd given a platform to me

00:21:04.590 --> 00:21:08.850 align:middle line:84%
for pseudo-science and that I
was accusing some scientists

00:21:08.850 --> 00:21:10.360 align:middle line:90%
of being dogmatic.

00:21:10.360 --> 00:21:12.575 align:middle line:90%
And this was so totally untrue.

00:21:12.575 --> 00:21:14.130 align:middle line:90%
And science wasn't dogmatic.

00:21:14.130 --> 00:21:17.100 align:middle line:84%
It was totally open-minded
and finding out the truth.

00:21:17.100 --> 00:21:20.040 align:middle line:84%
And they got so
angry about me saying

00:21:20.040 --> 00:21:23.310 align:middle line:84%
that science was dogmatic,
they insisted on TED

00:21:23.310 --> 00:21:26.086 align:middle line:84%
removing this from
their main website.

00:21:26.086 --> 00:21:27.780 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVID: And they
actually did it.

00:21:27.780 --> 00:21:28.950 align:middle line:84%
>>SHELDRAKE: And
TED actually did it.

00:21:28.950 --> 00:21:30.390 align:middle line:84%
They were frightened
by them, because they

00:21:30.390 --> 00:21:31.560 align:middle line:90%
thought these people--

00:21:31.560 --> 00:21:34.032 align:middle line:84%
they claimed to speak with
the authority of science.

00:21:34.032 --> 00:21:34.832 align:middle line:90%
[VIDEO PLAYBACK]

00:21:34.832 --> 00:21:36.780 align:middle line:84%
The science delusion
is the belief

00:21:36.780 --> 00:21:39.810 align:middle line:84%
that science already understands
the nature of reality

00:21:39.810 --> 00:21:44.070 align:middle line:84%
in principle, leaving any of
the details to be filled in.

00:21:44.070 --> 00:21:47.640 align:middle line:84%
This is a very widespread
belief in our society.

00:21:47.640 --> 00:21:50.440 align:middle line:84%
It's the kind of belief
system of people who say,

00:21:50.440 --> 00:21:53.340 align:middle line:84%
I don't believe in God,
I believe in science.

00:21:53.340 --> 00:21:56.270 align:middle line:84%
It's a belief system
which has now been

00:21:56.270 --> 00:21:57.515 align:middle line:90%
spread to the entire world.

00:21:57.515 --> 00:21:59.200 align:middle line:90%
[END PLAYBACK]

00:21:59.200 --> 00:22:02.970 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVID: So TED is supposed
to be ideas worth sharing.

00:22:02.970 --> 00:22:04.160 align:middle line:90%
Isn't that their logline?

00:22:04.160 --> 00:22:04.993 align:middle line:90%
>>SHELDRAKE: Mm-hmm.

00:22:04.993 --> 00:22:09.480 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVID: Now, in
a modern society,

00:22:09.480 --> 00:22:11.850 align:middle line:84%
with open information
available online,

00:22:11.850 --> 00:22:14.290 align:middle line:84%
shouldn't people be allowed
to make up their own minds

00:22:14.290 --> 00:22:15.930 align:middle line:84%
and survey the
evidence for themselves

00:22:15.930 --> 00:22:17.580 align:middle line:90%
and decide what is true?

00:22:17.580 --> 00:22:19.710 align:middle line:84%
TED's going to guard
the gate and not

00:22:19.710 --> 00:22:22.830 align:middle line:84%
even allow people to consider
that what you're saying

00:22:22.830 --> 00:22:23.917 align:middle line:90%
is true?

00:22:23.917 --> 00:22:26.250 align:middle line:84%
>>SHELDRAKE: Most people have
been bullied by people who

00:22:26.250 --> 00:22:28.080 align:middle line:84%
claim to speak in
the name of science,

00:22:28.080 --> 00:22:30.870 align:middle line:84%
who pull rank on them and
say, we know, and you don't.

00:22:30.870 --> 00:22:33.970 align:middle line:84%
I think they were
bullied into doing this.

00:22:33.970 --> 00:22:35.910 align:middle line:90%
And it was a major mistake.

00:22:35.910 --> 00:22:40.090 align:middle line:84%
It has done great
damage to their brand.

00:22:40.090 --> 00:22:42.080 align:middle line:90%
I think they recognize that now.

00:22:42.080 --> 00:22:43.500 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVID: And it
ended up actually

00:22:43.500 --> 00:22:45.620 align:middle line:84%
causing the video to be seen
by many more people, right?

00:22:45.620 --> 00:22:48.210 align:middle line:84%
>>SHELDRAKE: Exactly, because
Graham Hancock, whose talk was

00:22:48.210 --> 00:22:52.800 align:middle line:84%
also banned, told people they're
about to ban it, lots of people

00:22:52.800 --> 00:22:55.470 align:middle line:84%
put it up on websites
all over the internet.

00:22:55.470 --> 00:22:59.420 align:middle line:84%
When my TEDx talk was taken
down from their main site,

00:22:59.420 --> 00:23:01.470 align:middle line:90%
it had 35,000 views.

00:23:01.470 --> 00:23:04.540 align:middle line:84%
It's now had well over
a million worldwide.

00:23:04.540 --> 00:23:08.590 align:middle line:84%
And so in effect, this
is actually a good thing.

00:23:08.590 --> 00:23:12.900 align:middle line:84%
I mean, they actually
helped get the message out.

00:23:12.900 --> 00:23:15.570 align:middle line:84%
And I think one has to see
that in any process of paradigm

00:23:15.570 --> 00:23:20.190 align:middle line:84%
change, arguments and
controversy is inevitable.

00:23:20.190 --> 00:23:24.900 align:middle line:84%
You can't change the paradigm
without people seeing

00:23:24.900 --> 00:23:27.190 align:middle line:90%
how the arguments played out.

00:23:27.190 --> 00:23:29.250 align:middle line:84%
And in the case
of TED, the people

00:23:29.250 --> 00:23:32.810 align:middle line:84%
who were defending standard
scientific materialism

00:23:32.810 --> 00:23:36.000 align:middle line:84%
put up extraordinarily
weak arguments.

00:23:36.000 --> 00:23:39.150 align:middle line:84%
I mean, they were basically
appealing to authority,

00:23:39.150 --> 00:23:43.780 align:middle line:84%
their authority, and
indulging in verbal abuse,

00:23:43.780 --> 00:23:46.770 align:middle line:84%
ad hominem attacks on me
and on Graham Hancock.

00:23:46.770 --> 00:23:48.300 align:middle line:90%
>>DAVID: You now have your own--

00:23:48.300 --> 00:23:51.030 align:middle line:84%
or you're part of a
whistleblower site

00:23:51.030 --> 00:23:53.880 align:middle line:84%
that actually
investigates skeptics.

00:23:53.880 --> 00:23:56.940 align:middle line:90%
Talk to me about that.

00:23:56.940 --> 00:23:58.620 align:middle line:84%
>>SHELDRAKE: I
helped set up a site

00:23:58.620 --> 00:24:02.580 align:middle line:84%
10 years ago called
skepticalinvestigations.org,

00:24:02.580 --> 00:24:04.360 align:middle line:90%
which investigates skeptics.

00:24:04.360 --> 00:24:08.790 align:middle line:10%
And we've now updated it to
a new site, Skeptical About

00:24:08.790 --> 00:24:10.050 align:middle line:10%
Skeptics.

00:24:10.050 --> 00:24:16.200 align:middle line:10%
And this builds up dossiers
on individual media skeptics

00:24:16.200 --> 00:24:18.420 align:middle line:10%
and also organized skepticism.

00:24:18.420 --> 00:24:20.160 align:middle line:84%
Because most people
don't realize

00:24:20.160 --> 00:24:22.080 align:middle line:84%
there are
organizations whose job

00:24:22.080 --> 00:24:26.100 align:middle line:84%
it is to try and debunk
what they call claims

00:24:26.100 --> 00:24:27.750 align:middle line:84%
of the paranormal,
anything to do

00:24:27.750 --> 00:24:31.530 align:middle line:84%
with parapsychology, alternative
medicine, many aspects

00:24:31.530 --> 00:24:34.530 align:middle line:84%
of consciousness studies,
near-death experiences.

00:24:34.530 --> 00:24:36.630 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVID: Whole organizations
dedicated to this.

00:24:36.630 --> 00:24:36.990 align:middle line:90%
>>SHELDRAKE: Yes.

00:24:36.990 --> 00:24:38.448 align:middle line:84%
One of them is
called The Committee

00:24:38.448 --> 00:24:41.100 align:middle line:90%
for Skeptical Inquiry.

00:24:41.100 --> 00:24:44.430 align:middle line:84%
And it publishes a magazine
called the Skeptical Inquirer.

00:24:44.430 --> 00:24:46.670 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVID: And you said
you sent somebody in

00:24:46.670 --> 00:24:49.170 align:middle line:84%
to infiltrate one of
these conferences.

00:24:49.170 --> 00:24:50.070 align:middle line:90%
What did they see?

00:24:50.070 --> 00:24:51.528 align:middle line:84%
>>SHELDRAKE: Well,
they went to one

00:24:51.528 --> 00:24:53.670 align:middle line:90%
of these big skeptic congresses.

00:24:53.670 --> 00:24:55.830 align:middle line:84%
Basically, a lot of people
who are rather angry,

00:24:55.830 --> 00:25:01.440 align:middle line:84%
who want to have certainty, who
want to suppress what they see

00:25:01.440 --> 00:25:05.250 align:middle line:84%
as superstition and
pseudoscience, basically,

00:25:05.250 --> 00:25:08.250 align:middle line:84%
scientific reactionaries
who are clinging on

00:25:08.250 --> 00:25:10.770 align:middle line:84%
to an outmoded worldview
because it gives them

00:25:10.770 --> 00:25:12.600 align:middle line:90%
a sense of security.

00:25:12.600 --> 00:25:15.810 align:middle line:84%
And they're setting up
organizations with chapters.

00:25:15.810 --> 00:25:19.140 align:middle line:84%
One of the workshops they had
at one of these meetings in Las

00:25:19.140 --> 00:25:21.900 align:middle line:84%
Vegas called the
Amazing Meeting--

00:25:21.900 --> 00:25:26.000 align:middle line:84%
it was promoted by the Randi
organization, James Randi.

00:25:26.000 --> 00:25:28.920 align:middle line:84%
A workshop led by him
and Michael Shermer,

00:25:28.920 --> 00:25:33.120 align:middle line:84%
editor of the
Skeptic magazine, was

00:25:33.120 --> 00:25:35.010 align:middle line:90%
"How to be a Media Skeptic."

00:25:35.010 --> 00:25:36.560 align:middle line:84%
And they train
people how to do it.

00:25:36.560 --> 00:25:38.250 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVID: "How To Be
a Media Skeptic."

00:25:38.250 --> 00:25:39.060 align:middle line:90%
>>SHELDRAKE: Yes.

00:25:39.060 --> 00:25:42.530 align:middle line:84%
And the advertisement
for the workshop

00:25:42.530 --> 00:25:45.570 align:middle line:84%
said, "Be the guy the
media call the next time

00:25:45.570 --> 00:25:47.770 align:middle line:90%
a charlatan shows up in town."

00:25:47.770 --> 00:25:48.680 align:middle line:90%
>>DAVID: Really?

00:25:48.680 --> 00:25:51.090 align:middle line:84%
>>SHELDRAKE: And what they
have is trained people.

00:25:51.090 --> 00:25:54.720 align:middle line:84%
And then it says, you
don't have to have

00:25:54.720 --> 00:25:57.150 align:middle line:84%
any particular
qualifications to do this.

00:25:57.150 --> 00:25:59.920 align:middle line:84%
Just behave as if you've
got the authority.

00:25:59.920 --> 00:26:00.720 align:middle line:90%
And then it says--

00:26:00.720 --> 00:26:01.553 align:middle line:90%
>>DAVID: Oh, my god.

00:26:01.553 --> 00:26:04.200 align:middle line:84%
>>SHELDRAKE: And then it says,
found a local skeptics society.

00:26:04.200 --> 00:26:07.170 align:middle line:84%
It said, if necessary, you can
be the president, the chairman,

00:26:07.170 --> 00:26:09.510 align:middle line:90%
and the secretary yourself.

00:26:09.510 --> 00:26:12.500 align:middle line:84%
So you create an organization
that looks credible.

00:26:12.500 --> 00:26:15.720 align:middle line:84%
You then, every time
someone shows up

00:26:15.720 --> 00:26:18.020 align:middle line:84%
who's promoting alternative
medicine, parapsychology,

00:26:18.020 --> 00:26:20.340 align:middle line:84%
or anything like
that, the media like

00:26:20.340 --> 00:26:24.450 align:middle line:84%
having someone they can ring
up, your number in their files

00:26:24.450 --> 00:26:27.570 align:middle line:84%
that they can just call
for the alternative view.

00:26:27.570 --> 00:26:29.100 align:middle line:90%
And you're the guy they call.

00:26:29.100 --> 00:26:31.320 align:middle line:84%
And then you just say,
this guy is a charlatan.

00:26:31.320 --> 00:26:33.060 align:middle line:90%
The stuff's been discredited.

00:26:33.060 --> 00:26:35.640 align:middle line:84%
It's not scientifically
credible, etc.

00:26:35.640 --> 00:26:38.550 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVID: Did they teach them
to target the personal attacks

00:26:38.550 --> 00:26:41.170 align:middle line:90%
instead of the actual data?

00:26:41.170 --> 00:26:41.970 align:middle line:90%
>>SHELDRAKE: Yes.

00:26:41.970 --> 00:26:43.850 align:middle line:84%
It's largely by
focusing on people

00:26:43.850 --> 00:26:47.370 align:middle line:84%
and saying they're
charlatans, or just saying

00:26:47.370 --> 00:26:49.620 align:middle line:90%
their data has been discredited.

00:26:49.620 --> 00:26:51.150 align:middle line:90%
They don't go into detail.

00:26:51.150 --> 00:26:53.950 align:middle line:84%
Most of them know nothing
about the details.

00:26:53.950 --> 00:26:57.570 align:middle line:84%
So we're not dealing
here with just people

00:26:57.570 --> 00:27:00.620 align:middle line:84%
using normal skeptical
commonsense skepticism.

00:27:00.620 --> 00:27:02.840 align:middle line:84%
We're dealing with an
ideologically motivated

00:27:02.840 --> 00:27:07.130 align:middle line:84%
campaign that is well organized,
that has local chapters, that

00:27:07.130 --> 00:27:10.670 align:middle line:84%
has national organizations,
international organizations,

00:27:10.670 --> 00:27:16.250 align:middle line:84%
and whose agenda is to
roll back the alternative

00:27:16.250 --> 00:27:18.740 align:middle line:84%
and complementary medicine,
integrative medicine,

00:27:18.740 --> 00:27:23.210 align:middle line:84%
holistic science,
parapsychology, consciousness

00:27:23.210 --> 00:27:27.260 align:middle line:84%
studies in the name of an
extreme form of materialism,

00:27:27.260 --> 00:27:30.620 align:middle line:90%
a dogmatic materialism.

00:27:30.620 --> 00:27:32.690 align:middle line:84%
So it's not just
individual opinions.

00:27:32.690 --> 00:27:35.420 align:middle line:84%
We're dealing with
organized efforts here.

00:27:35.420 --> 00:27:39.000 align:middle line:84%
And that's what in our website,
Skeptical About Skeptics,

00:27:39.000 --> 00:27:43.790 align:middle line:84%
we're informing people about
and documenting the activities

00:27:43.790 --> 00:27:45.426 align:middle line:90%
of these media skeptics.

00:27:45.426 --> 00:27:47.300 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVID: So what do you
have coming up ahead?

00:27:47.300 --> 00:27:48.950 align:middle line:84%
What's your next
big thing people

00:27:48.950 --> 00:27:51.560 align:middle line:84%
can be looking out for so
that you continue this battle

00:27:51.560 --> 00:27:55.430 align:middle line:84%
and fight the good fight
to educate humanity?

00:27:55.430 --> 00:28:00.290 align:middle line:84%
>>SHELDRAKE: Well, I'm
part of a group that met,

00:28:00.290 --> 00:28:05.250 align:middle line:84%
a group of scientists
that met in February 2014

00:28:05.250 --> 00:28:09.050 align:middle line:84%
in Tucson, Arizona called
the Postmaterialist Summit.

00:28:09.050 --> 00:28:11.660 align:middle line:84%
And what we're doing
is trying to move

00:28:11.660 --> 00:28:13.520 align:middle line:84%
towards a
post-materialist science,

00:28:13.520 --> 00:28:16.310 align:middle line:84%
so we can have science
that's still science.

00:28:16.310 --> 00:28:19.010 align:middle line:84%
I and my colleagues are
all very pro-science.

00:28:19.010 --> 00:28:20.720 align:middle line:84%
But we think science
should be liberated

00:28:20.720 --> 00:28:24.335 align:middle line:84%
from this dogmatic
constraint of materialism.

00:28:24.335 --> 00:28:26.960 align:middle line:84%
We think it would be better and
more productive, more exciting,

00:28:26.960 --> 00:28:28.860 align:middle line:90%
more interesting.

00:28:28.860 --> 00:28:34.500 align:middle line:84%
And we're launching a website
called opensciences.org,

00:28:34.500 --> 00:28:37.970 align:middle line:84%
which is a portal for the more
open-minded research going

00:28:37.970 --> 00:28:39.545 align:middle line:90%
on in the sciences today.

00:28:39.545 --> 00:28:41.490 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVID: I'll have
to check that out.

00:28:41.490 --> 00:28:43.441 align:middle line:84%
So the books that
you're working on,

00:28:43.441 --> 00:28:44.690 align:middle line:90%
do you have a book coming out?

00:28:44.690 --> 00:28:47.670 align:middle line:84%
Or what are you
doing in that front?

00:28:47.670 --> 00:28:49.970 align:middle line:10%
>>SHELDRAKE: Well, the main
book I'm still working on

00:28:49.970 --> 00:28:53.090 align:middle line:10%
at the moment is my "Science Set
Free," "The Science Delusion,"

00:28:53.090 --> 00:28:56.115 align:middle line:10%
in the sense that I'm
following up the kinds of ideas

00:28:56.115 --> 00:28:56.915 align:middle line:10%
that are there.

00:28:56.915 --> 00:28:59.330 align:middle line:10%
But I have a book coming
out with Matthew Fox,

00:28:59.330 --> 00:29:04.040 align:middle line:10%
the theologian, called
"The Physics of Angels."

00:29:04.040 --> 00:29:07.730 align:middle line:84%
And this is a whole big topic
we don't have time to get into.

00:29:07.730 --> 00:29:10.880 align:middle line:84%
But what we're doing is looking
at the idea of consciousness

00:29:10.880 --> 00:29:13.540 align:middle line:90%
beyond the human level.

00:29:13.540 --> 00:29:15.350 align:middle line:84%
In all traditional
societies, people

00:29:15.350 --> 00:29:17.750 align:middle line:84%
thought there were many
levels of consciousness

00:29:17.750 --> 00:29:20.720 align:middle line:90%
beyond the human level.

00:29:20.720 --> 00:29:22.640 align:middle line:84%
In the Middle Ages, they
thought, for example,

00:29:22.640 --> 00:29:26.180 align:middle line:84%
that each star had a
mind or an intelligence,

00:29:26.180 --> 00:29:28.620 align:middle line:84%
which they called the
angel of that star.

00:29:28.620 --> 00:29:30.620 align:middle line:84%
And so the star
was like the body,

00:29:30.620 --> 00:29:34.135 align:middle line:84%
and the angel was the mind
or intelligence of that star.

00:29:34.135 --> 00:29:35.510 align:middle line:84%
So what we do in
the book is look

00:29:35.510 --> 00:29:38.600 align:middle line:84%
at traditional Western ideas
on angels, which were not,

00:29:38.600 --> 00:29:41.150 align:middle line:84%
of course, of men
with colored wings.

00:29:41.150 --> 00:29:44.210 align:middle line:84%
They were the idea of
cosmic intelligences

